{{Infobox organization |name = Dhaka Ladies Club |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1951 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://dlc-bd.com/ Dhaka Ladies Club] |remarks = }}
'''Dhaka Ladies Club''' is a club for "elite" women in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="wen" /> Jahanara Munnan is the present president of the club.<ref>{{cite web|title=Khaleda asks Hasina to quit power like UK PM Cameron|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/politics/khaleda-asks-hasina-quit-power-uk-pm-cameron-1246519|website=thedailystar.net|publisher=The Daily Star|accessdate=27 September 2016|date=27 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jahanara president, Towhida secretary general of Dhaka Ladies Club|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/city/jahanara-president-towhida-secretary-general-dhaka-ladies-club-1218853|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=27 September 2016|date=4 May 2016}}</ref>
==History== The Club was opened in 1951 by a selected number of "elite" women. The founder of the club was Shamsia Shahbuddin who was the wife of the then Chief Justice' of [[East Pakistan]] Justice Shahabuddin. In 1955 one acre of land was bought in [[Eskaton]], Dhaka by the then President of the club, Begum Amiruddin.<ref name="wen">{{cite web|title=Dhaka Ladies Club, The|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Dhaka_Ladies_Club,_The|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref>
The club was registered under Joint Stock companies Act in 1960. The club is run 16 members Executive Committee who are elected for terms of three years. The club runs regular and music schools for underprivileged children in Dhaka.<ref name="wen" /> Former Prime Minister [[Khaleda Zia]] holds press conferences in the club auditorium.<ref>{{cite web|title=Country turned into ‘police state’: Khaleda|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/politics/country-turned-police-state-khaleda-1243813|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=27 September 2016|date=22 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AL behind secret killings: Khaleda|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/politics/al-behind-secret-killings-khaleda-1247089|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=27 September 2016|date=28 June 2016}}</ref>
