{{use Indian English|date=February 2014}} {{use dmy dates|date=February 2014}} {{Multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=November 2017}} {{cleanup infobox}} }} {{Infobox actress | name = Gautami / Thadimala | image = Gauthami.jpg | caption = | birth_date = 02-07 cite a reliable source for date of birth --> | birth_place = Tadimalla | birth_name = Gautami Tadimalla | othername = | alma_mater = | website = www.lifeagainfoundation.org | nationality = {{flagu|India}}n | occupation = [[Actress]], social Worker | yearsactive = 1986{{ndash}}present | residence = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]] | spouse =Bharat Bhatia | partner = [[Kamal Haasan]] (2004-2016) | children = 3 }}
'''Gautami Tadimalla''' is an [[Indian film]] actress who has worked mainly in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] films, although she also appeared in successful films in [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Malayalam]], [[Hindi]] and [[Kannada]] cinema. She is also a television actress, television host “LifeAgainFoundation founder and costume designer.<ref name="rediff1999">[http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/jun/12gau.htm Rediff On The NeT, Movies: An interview with Gauthami]. Rediff.com (1999-06-12). Retrieved on 2012-07-11.</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=A banquet of ideas at TEDx Chennai|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/a-banquet-of-ideas-at-tedx-chennai/article3952146.ece|accessdate=15 August 2016|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date=1 October 2012|language=en-IN}}</ref>
==Film career== Gautami went to [[GITAM University]] in Visakhapatnam to pursue Engineering. She made her first appearance at the age of 17 in the Telugu film ''Dayamayudu'', that was produced by her cousin.<ref name="rediff1999"/><ref name="hindu2007">[http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/07/20/stories/2007072051240400.htm Friday Review Chennai: Interview: Determined to make a mark, again], ''The Hindu'', 20 July 2007; retrieved 11 July 2012.</ref>
She was introduced to Tamil films through ''[[Guru Sishyan (1988 film)|Guru Shishyan]]'', a film that starred [[Rajinikanth]] and [[Prabhu Ganesan|Prabhu]].<ref name="rediff1999"/> She was most active in Tamil cinema from 1987 to 1998 and was a tough competitor to the other heroines of her time, [[Kushboo]] and [[Bhanupriya]]. Her filmography includes classics like ''[[Apoorva Sagodharargal (1989 film)|Apoorva Sagodharargal]]'', ''[[Raja Chinna Roja]]'', ''[[Thevar Magan]]'', ''[[Panakkaran]]'', ''[[Guru Sishyan (1988 film)|Guru Sishyan]]'', ''[[Ooru Vittu Ooru Vanthu]]'', ''[[Dharma Durai]]'', ''[[Rickshaw Mama]]'' as well as Mani Ratnam's ''[[Iruvar]]'' (1997), which co-starred [[Mohanlal]], [[Prakash Raj]], [[Aishwarya Rai]], [[Tabu (actress)|Tabu]], Nassar and [[Revathi]].
She has acted in the Tamil serial ''Indira'' in the lead role. She made a guest appearance in the song "Chikku Bukku Railu" with [[Prabhu Deva]] in the film ''Gentleman''.<ref name="rediff1999"/> She had hosted a [[talk show]] in [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] titled ''Anbudan'' which was launched to compete with ''[[Koffee with Anu]]'' running on [[STAR Vijay]].<ref name="hindu2007"/> She acted in the serial [[Abirami (TV series)|Abirami]] which was telecast on Kalaignar TV.<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-25/news-interviews/28062517_1_small-screen-gauthami-kamal-haasan Gauthami enters small screen – Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (2009-11-25). Retrieved on 2012-07-11.</ref> She made a comeback to the film industry in the late 2000s as a costume designer for films starring her partner [[Kamal Haasan]]. She won the [[Vijay Award for Best Costume Designer]] for ''[[Dasavathaaram]]''.<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/47587.html Univercell 3rd Vijay Awards – Winners List – Tamil Movie News]. IndiaGlitz (2009-06-15). Retrieved on 2012-07-11.</ref> After sixteen years, she returned to acting by starring in the Tamil film ''[[Papanasam (film)|Papanasam]]'' in which she was paired with her partner [[Kamal Haasan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Give timely support to good films, Kamal tells media|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/give-timely-support-to-good-films-kamal-tells-media/article7401083.ece?homepage=true&w=ma446|accessdate=15 August 2016|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|date=9 July 2015|language=en-IN}}</ref>
She was diagnosed with breast cancer at the age of 35,<ref>[http://chennaionline.com/movies/star-track/20122709042706/Gauthami-Dont-feel-scared-of-breast-cancer.col Gauthami: ‘Don’t feel scared of breast cancer’ | startrack – Movies]. ChennaiOnline (2012-03-09). Retrieved on 2012-07-11.</ref> and recovered from it.<ref>[http://www.hindu.com/2009/03/09/stories/2009030957530300.htm Gautami narrates her experience of fighting breast cancer] ''[[The Hindu]]''</ref><ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-03-10/news-interviews/28013191_1_breast-cancer-films-kamal-haasan Don’t let mediocrity be the standard:Kamal] ''[[The Times of India]]''</ref><ref>[http://indiatoday.intodaylte/Story/5476/Simply%20Chennai/It%27s+the+genes+at+play.html It's the genes at play] ''[[India Today]]''</ref>
