The '''Miroslaw Romanowski Medal''' is awarded annually by the [[Royal Society of Canada]] "for significant contributions to the resolution of scientific aspects of environmental problems or for important improvements to the quality of an ecosystem in all aspects - terrestrial, atmospheric and aqueous - brought about by scientific means". <ref> {{cite web|url= http://www.rsc-src.ca/en/miroslaw-romanowski-medal|title= Miroslaw Romanowski Medal|publisher= Royal Society of Canada|accessdate = 22 November 2015}} </ref>
Established in 1994, the medal is named in honour of the metrologist [[Mirosław Romanowski]].
==Recipients== Source: [https://rsc-src.ca/en/past-award-winners#Romanowski Royal Society of Canada]
{{Columns-list|colwidth=30em| * 2017 - [[Keith Hipel]], FRSC * 2016 - [[Mark Boyce]], FRSC <ref> {{cite web|url=http://wildlife.org/mark-boyce-awarded-prestigious-miroslaw-romanowski-medal/|title=Mark Boyce awarded prestigious Miroslaw Romanowski Medal|publisher=The Wildlife Society|accessdate= 2 December 2016}} </ref> * 2015 - [[R. Kerry Rowe]], FRSC * 2014 - [[Yves Bergeron (scientist)|Yves Bergeron]], FRSC * 2013 - John Giesy, FRSC * 2012 - Catherine Potvin * 2011 - [[Andrew J. Weaver]], FRSC * 2010 - Donald Mackay * 2009 - [[Stan Boutin]], FRSC * 2008 - Warwick F. Vincent, FRSC * 2007 - [[Christopher Wood (biologist)|Christopher M. Wood]] * 2006 - [[Richard Peltier]] * 2005 - Robie Macdonald, FRSC * 2004 - Derek C.G. Muir, FRSC * 2003 - Peter J. Dillon * 2002 - Kevin J. Kennedy * 2001 - [[John P. Smol]], FRSC * 2000 - David R.S. Lean * 1999 - Howard Roy Krouse, FRSC & Jerome O. Nriagu, FRSC * 1998 - Thomas C. Hutchinson, FRSC * 1997 - Michel Maldague * 1996 - John A. Cherry, FRSC & Robert W. Gillham * 1995 - [[Pierre Legendre (ecologist)|Pierre Legendre]], MSRC * 1994 - [[David Schindler|David W. Schindler]], FRSC }}
